caption: Tacos are really great!!! The guy that serves is so cool...he really knows his stuff..so fast and efficient. You can eat in too which is great!!! Love to visit at lunchtime for my 3 soft flour tacos..yum 😋 😋 😋.
Absolutely terrible service. Employees were rude and rushed every order. They also were out of chicken and fish when I was there. Food tasted okay , but overall not a good experience.
5 dollar giant breakfast burritos.  Closest thing you can get to a chipotle in hawaii
Wow super tasty 😋😋 I ordered the burrito and I was not disappointed!!!

This place is one of the absolute best place to have lunch if you're in the mood for Mexican food. The owner who you would find there working, is a blast to talk to. Order the carne asada fries.its the best.  Tell me I'm wrong.
Good service
The food here is delicious and the customer service is amazing! Everything on the menu is really good but the burrito bowl with chicken, brown rice, pinto and guac is my favorite.
Its so good I see it in my dreams. The only con is that you arent there right now. Go out and go buy their stuff its amazing.
Ive been around the world and this is my favorite.  Fresh fresh fresh
This was my favorite place for lunch when I was working in downtown Honolulu! I loved the burrito bowls!
I tried it a few weeks ago and have been back several times since for the delicious breakfast burrito! I've brought vegetarian friend and meat-eater friend and they both love it too!

I went back to this place for lunch and being a Google guide I ask review questions. Well the dirty dread head that takes your order was rude and completely snide about. answeing any questions the Google guide asks. So they don't care about customer info, only your DOUGH. So my review is 1 STAR because it's the lowest you can actually rank them.
Amazing and delicious. Breakfast burrito for only $5. The Owner/Manager very friendly.  Employees awesome service and it was quick. Highly recommend
Best burritos on island!  Good quality meats, many choices and friendly staff.  They have quesadillas,  bowls, burritos, tacos, fish tacos and more.
Best Burrito Bowl downtown
Come hungry! Fast and delicious. They have a secret, uber-hot sauce that you have to ask for if searing your taste buds is something you enjoy.
This is where I go in town to get a quick two taco lunch.
Their breakfast burritos were advised to me, I havent had them in over a year and I miss them.
A little noisy.  Great guacamole and generous portions.
Quality Mexican food for the low!!!
Can be a little busy but it's just about the best Mexican food you're gonna find around here.

If you’re looking for something to believe in, you’ve found it! The best authentic food with excellent value and generous portions! Everyone on the other side of the counter will make you smile as they provide you with a fantastic experience and choice food served with Aloha! Go BIC Tacos!!
Pulled pork tacos
Best place for lunch downtown! Quick, healthy options and delicious! Yummy!  🤩🌮 🌯🥙😍

For mainlanders - BIC Tacos is about as close as you'll get to a Chipotle on Oahu.  Good, basic Mexican style meals at reasonable prices. Portion sizes more than justify the menu prices. Very popular during the weekday lunch rush; servers work quickly but the line can get quite long.
I love BIC City’s Tacos. The best taco joint I’ve ever been to. Since I’ve moved, i haven’t found one even close to them. Soooo Ono!!
Okay Tacos
Buy 3 tacos and get 1 free on Fridays 😋
Good food and fast service.

Recently I was visiting Honolulu on a business trip and I was missing good Mexican food from my hometown in San Diego. A friend suggested BIC Taco as the place to go.   I was pleasantly surprised! Clean, friendly service from Michael the chef and Rosalia behind the counter and most importantly a great tasting breakfast  burrito! It is amazing all the choices you get to load your burrito with. I wish we had these in San Diego. Don't forget to grab an Haagen Daaz ice cream for desert. Hats off to Michael and Rosalia! Thank you!
They serve their breakfast tacos all day!
Great fresh and fast Mexican.  The Breakfast  Buritto is excellent and a great value.
Great breakfast burritos. BIC Tacos offered exactly what I was craving.

Amazing food, extremely nice owner and super friendly and helpful staff. We had the fish tacos which were so delicious with the spicy mayo, cilantro and green salsa. The owner was super helpful when we asked for directions and local advise and the staff were very friendly to us when we ordered, asking where we’re from, etc. Great place with amazing food.

Great place for lunch in downtown area and food is excellent. But be prepared to wait in line which is often out the door and onto the sidewalk by 12:30pm. Best to go at or before 12pm or wait until closer to 1pm when the line is not so long. When you get to the counter, food prep is quick once you place your order. Most people seem to get their food to go, but there's plenty of seating indoors and outdoors if you have time to stay and eat there.
Phenomenal food and great value.  Fast service  too.  Highly recommend
Best Burrito and taco joint on the island!
Great taco place.  Burritos, tacos. Carnes, fish. All you can ask for.
Friendly service.  Fast service.  Very busy place for lunch.

Staff is cool. Food is okay. Best part is it's fast and filing. The ingredients are different than traditional Mexican food so there isn't really a good comparison there. Despite the average food, I go here pretty often, mostly because it's fast and close by. It's worth a try to see if it satisfies your palate.
Burrito made to order! Add hot queso! Add Jalepenos, careful asking for the hot salsa, you may end up with sweaty eyelids.

BIC Tacos has excellent ingredients making up great food and terrific service. Like many Mexican taco places you walk through the line and tell the staff what you want starting with tortillas through the protein, veggies, and salsa hotness. The salsa options are all good. Hot is actually hot. There may be a line at lunch but it goes pretty quickly. They do have specials during the week such as cheaper fountain drinks or free taco when you buy three. Great lunch option downtown. Prices are also reasonable.
Amazing flavorful food! Great and fast service.  Everyone is always so friendly.
Service is great, staff are friendly and quick.
Great service, very large burrito bowls. The hottest sauce is VERY HOT! I recommend getting it on the side - I can eat habanero peppers whole but this sauce gets me every time!
ONO food!!  The Owner, Mike, and his team are friendly and fast! By far, the best Horchata on the island....try the one with coconut!! Yummy!!
Good product

Absolutely love BIC Tacos! I have had the pleasure of eating almost every item on the menu and I can definitely say -  this is the most AWESOME Mexican restaurant and gathering place to get your money’s worth! Large burrito , plenty of meat, perfect size of vegetables, loaded with cheese, offers all different kinds of fillings on your burrito, lettuce pick, corn, cheese, their mild sauce and BBQ sauce is Out of this world!! I’m a spicy kind of girl and I love it when the chile tingles my lips when i eat it.  I had the pleasure of getting to know the owner of the restaurant Michael, passionate at what he does and his fiancé Nyra has been very supportive. Great people who know a lot about excellent service . The area is clean, restrooms are superb. My favorite menu item would have to be the breakfast burrito. It’s served all day (yassss) and the burrito is huge!! I would have showed you pictures but I was too hungry - sorry. I have eaten at this place between 2-3 times a week with something different each time. Oh yeah! It’s that great!  My burritos whether breakfast or lunch burritos have always stayed together in terms of within the tortilla without falling apart. If your burrito is falling apart while you’re eating then you don’t know how to eat a burrito. Their chips and queso are also so fresh. My left over nachos with the dip was so large I had to pack it and take home with me and reheat them in the oven. I could almost say that this place is my “go to lunch place” it’s about four blocks from my work place and it’s so worth it. The walk compensates it and I get a head start with digestion.  BICs is Locates on the beautiful side and heart of Chinatown so don’t worry about the homeless walking around or the strong odor of smelling like urine. If you have not eaten at BICs yet- you’re missing out! Give them a try! It took me one bite of my loaded carne chicken burrito and I was in love. I Highly recommend this place. Large variety of Food, awesome television, great bathrooms, cool refreshments, and OMG ice cream!!!! Thank you BICs for feeding me during Lunchtime especially with such a high stressful job! Keep up the great work Michael!! See you on Monday!!!
Always great food
Great kind service. The food was fresh and delicious.
Food is great.  Nice touch on the ice icream with the order!

The street tacos were great and only $2 every day! My hubby had the pork belly bacon burrito with eggs and loved it as well. The horchata is nice and sweet and cinnamon-y and the staff + owner are very kind. Oh, and the lunch line does look long but moves really fast. Definitely recommend.

We love BIC Tacos! This is one of our favorite lunch spots in downtown Honolulu! There is usually a line out the door, but it moves pretty quickly. My husband always gets a burrito, and I like to switch between tacos, salad, and nachos. Prices are reasonable and the servings are pretty big!
The steak and egg burrito is good! The hot sauce is nice and spicy. Nice clean place. Even though the line is long at lunch it moves fast. Keep that tinfoil on and save you a mess.
I've eaten here twice and really enjoyed both meals.  I highly recommend the tacos.  Great little place.  Don't be put off if the line is out the door, because it moves quickly.
Best "Mexican food"-burritos  in the island
Great tacos
Great food served quickly.  My favorite is their kalua pork crispy tacos.
Delicious 🤗
Excellent Mexican food. Very busy at lunch time... Sometimes there’s a line out the door... Totally worth it
Best tacos!!! Good value for the money and the owner Mike is super friendly.
High quality and great staff.  If it’s your first visit go early.  Ordering is a bit hectic and there are a lot of options.  Think of it as custom tacos.
Taco Tuesday you get a free ice cream or on Friday you buy three tacos and get one free. Love it here.
The pulled pork taco is outstanding!  It really is to die for!

I personally love Bic City Tacos.  The food is good, location is pretty clean when I go, burritos are massive and delicious. The biggest issue with them is the meat is drenched in juices so it gets the burritos soggy and messy while you eat. Minor problem for me but may bother others more.

Hawaii's version of Chipotle, but I think they do a better job. The salsa is certainly spicier and the servings are generous. Yesterday they were giving away free ice cream with each meal. Can't beat that. The only reason I docked them a star is because this annoying street performer (called himself a mentalist) was in the restaurant disturbing guests. I didn't want to deal with him. I was there with friends trying to catch up during lunch. I went there for food and a table, not to be harassed by a street performer.
Big burritos and 3 tacos for a decent price. Tuesday's is free ice cream.

Place is nice and open with a lot of tables to sit at. Clean with great workers who are polite.  I ordered a burrito with everything. BEWARE guacamole is $1.99 extra!😲 portions are big... taste well 🤔 a bit all over the place. Carna sada was very tasteful. I could have gone without the lime, and onion sautee which is a bit tangy for my liking. I should have stuck with ordering a taco.
Totally upbeat and delish
Best tacos I've ever had, very clean, affordable, delicious and Michael the manager is the best ever!!!

(Translated by Google) A perfectly decent place, the food is excellent. The waiters' attention and relevance was superb. The only missing part is the valet no AQ we were surprised where we will put our car amk.  (Original) Gayet nezih bir yer yemekleri mükemmel. Garsonların ilgi ve alakası ise süperdi. Tek eksik yanı vale yok aq arabamızı nereye koyacağız şaşırdık amk.
I like the queso nachos. Flavor(s) are different than other Mexican places.
Great burritos and the staff are always very nice and courteous.
I was not a fan of the taste but it was great value portion wise
Good burrito bowls and nachos bowls
I loved it. Very good food, great service and a clean comfortable place in town.
Decent Mexican food.  On Tuesdays you can get free ice cream with purchase of $10 or more...
Great food, decent prices, and great customer service.
Good food and nice folks!
Good food, reasonable prices, fast service (even with a constant line)
Awesome tacos
The have good customer service and also good burritos and tacos
very good & cheap & fast food
Very flavourful, tasty loved it. We went on Tuesday and they had free ice cream with $12 purchase. We go here couple of times a week for lunch.
Formerly Big City Tacos at the Hickam passenger terminal. Great burritos and bowls! Make sure to check out there other location at the Kapolei Commons.
